12. Qa3 (12. Rxb5 $2 axb5 13. Qxa8 Qxe5 $19) 12... Qxe5 13. Bf4 (13. Bxa8 $6 {
was played in Hedman-Leenhouts, Riga 2018, but here Black should go for} b4 $1
14. Rxb4 Bxb4 15. Qxb4 Qb5 $1 $15 {and White's compensation is insufficient.})
13... Qf6 14. Bxc7 {and here Black has an important choice:} b4 (14... Be5 15.
Bxe5 Qxe5 16. Bxa8 Qc7 (16... f6 $6 17. Rfd1 Kf7 $2 {was played in
Huzman-Mikhalevski,A Israel 2020 and now by means of} 18. Rd6 $1 {White could
have retained a decisive grip on Black's position.}) 17. Bg2 $1 f6 ({Perhaps
Black's most stubborn attempt is} 17... Qe7 {though} 18. Qe3 Qc7 19. Rfd1 O-O
20. Qd4 {followed by 21.Qd6 is very unpleasant for Black.}) (17... Nd7 $2 {
is met by} 18. Qc3 $1 {and Black isn't in time stabilizing his queenside, e.g.}
O-O 19. a4 Bb7 20. Bxb7 Qxb7 21. axb5 axb5 22. Qxc4 $18) ({Another instructive
line goes} 17... Bd7 $6 18. Rfd1 f6 19. Rd6 Kf7 20. Rbd1 Rc8 21. Be4 g6 $2 22.
Qe3 {and Black's kingside is too vulnerable.}) 18. Rfd1 $1 ({More accurate than
} 18. Qe3 Kf7 19. a4 Bd7 20. axb5 Bxb5 21. Rfd1 Nd7 22. Rd4 Rc8 {with about
equality in Wojtaszek-Roser, Aix les Bains 2011.}) 18... Kf7 (18... Nd7 19. Rd6
Ne5 20. f4 Qa7+ 21. Kh1 Ng4 22. h3 Qe3 23. Qa5 $1 Nf2+ 24. Kh2 Kf7 25. Bf3 h5
26. Rd8 Rxd8 27. Qxd8 Qc5 28. Qh8 {and White is winning in
