and the endgame is just too bad for Black, as his queenside majority is easily
stopped.} f5 22. Rb6 Rd8 23. Rxd8 Kxd8 24. Rxb8 Kc7 25. Rxc8+ Kxc8 26. Kf1 {
and White's winning, as confirmed by the following two games which are worth
playing through:} Kc7 27. Ke1 a5 28. Kd2 Kd6 29. Bb7 Kc5 (29... b4 30. Ba6 Kc5
31. Bc8 Kd6 32. Ke3 Kd5 33. Bd7 g5 34. Be8 e5 35. Kd2 f4 36. g4 Kd4 37. Bd7 Kd5
38. Bf5 h6 39. a4 Kc5 40. Bh7 Kd6 41. Bg8 c3+ 42. Kd3 e4+ 43. Kc2 Kc5 44. e3
Kc6 45. Ba2 Kc5 46. Kb3 Kd6 47. Bb1 {1-0 Frendzas-Morcin, LSS email 2013.}) 30.
Bc8 Kd5 31. h4 b4 32. Bd7 Kd6 33. Ba4 Kd5 34. e3 Ke4 35. Bc6+ Ke5 36. h5 Kd6
37. Ba4 Kc5 38. Bc2 h6 39. f4 Kb5 40. Bd1 Kc5 41. e4 Kd4 42. exf5 exf5 43. Bc2
Kd5 44. Bxf5 a4 45. Bg6 Kd4 46. Bf7 Kc5 47. Be8 a3 48. Kc2 Kd4 49. Bf7 Kc5 50.
g4 Kd4 51. Bxc4 Kxc4 52. g5 Kd5 53. Kb3 Ke6 54. gxh6 gxh6 55. Kxb4 Kd5 56. Kxa3
