15. Rxb4 Bxb4 16. Qxb4 a5 17. Qb5+ Bd7 18. Qxc4 (18. Qb6 $6 Na6 19. Bxa8 Nxc7
20. Qxc7 Qd8 21. Qa7 O-O {is unproblematic for Black in Fridman-Naiditsch,
Dortmund 2012.}) 18... Na6 (18... Ra6 19. Bxb8 Rb6 20. Bf4 (20. Ba7 Rb4 21. Qc7
