{[%evp 0,40,29,33,28,7,7,7,7,-15,-19,-19,36,33,17,17,24,-3,-3,-3,35,-64,-57,
-57,-11,-41,-35,8,12,12,22,40,14,-6,-5,-8,-6,2,7,7,6,1,1]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6
3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 a6 6. O-O Nc6 7. Na3 $6 {has been tried in various
games, but isn't promising White anything from a theoretical point of view.
Nevertheless, the ensuing positions are very tricky and White retains
reasonable practical chances if Black isn't alert. Now Black should respond
with} Bxa3 $1 8. bxa3 Rb8 $1 {and now the following sequence seems quite
standard} 9. Bb2 O-O 10. Qc2 b5 11. Rad1 Ne7 12. e4 Bb7 13. Rfe1 (13. d5 $2 {
doesn't work, in view of} exd5 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. exd5 Bxd5 16. Nh4 c6 $19 {
and White doesn't have enough compensation in Krasenkow-Petrosian,A Tallinn
1988.}) (13. Ne5 Nd7 14. f4 f5 $1 {I like this response.} 15. d5 {was seen in
Kozul-Petrosian,A Belgrade 1988 and now} Nxe5 16. Bxe5 exd5 17. exd5 Bxd5 18.
Qb2 c6 $1 19. Bxg7 (19. Bxb8 Qxb8 $17) 19... Rf7 {is favoring Black.}) 13...
Ng6 14. Bc3 {was seen in Khalifman-Akopian, Manila 1992 and here i propose} (
14. d5 $2 {is premature, e.g.} exd5 15. e5 Nd7 16. h4 {and now in Rogers,
J-Emerson, Reading 2016, Black could have played} Re8 $1 17. h5 Ngf8 18. h6 c5
$1 19. hxg7 Ne6 {followed by ...d5-d4 with a decisive advantage.}) (14. h4 $5 {
an useful move, preparing h4-h5. The only drawback is that this square is
temporarily covered. Hence, a waiting move in reply makes sense, e.g.} Re8 {
, clearing the f8-square for a knight retreat. The position remains
strategically complex position, but I would rather be Black. In the following
game, White quickly lost thread after} ({The point of White's last move is to
meet} 14... c5 $6 {with} 15. d5 exd5 16. exd5 {and now} Nxd5 $2 {runs into} 17.
h5 Nge7 18. Ng5 {with a crushing attack.}) 15. Rd2 $2 {and now in
Gazarek-Sveshnikov, Ljubljana 1996, Black could have considered} c5 $1 {as} 16.
d5 {isn't very attractive as Black trades one pair of rooks, slowing down
White's initiative.}) 14... c5 $1 15. dxc5 (15. d5 $2 exd5 16. exd5 Nxd5 {
and I don't see a good follow-up.}) 15... Qc7 $15 {and Black is in good shape.}
*

